# External Link Metadata for Blog Posts

When adding external links in blog posts, automatically scrape metadata using firecrawl-mcp to populate preview popover information.

## Process

1. **Identify External Links**: When adding a link to an external site in a blog post
2. **Use firecrawl-mcp**: Call the firecrawl-mcp tool to scrape the target URL
3. **Extract Metadata**: Get title, description, image, and other relevant metadata
4. **Populate Preview Info**: Use the scraped metadata to fill in the preview popover component

## Example

When adding a link like:

```markdown
Check out [this article](https://example.com/article)
```

Use firecrawl-mcp to scrape `https://example.com/article` and enhance it with preview metadata:

```markdown
<LinkWithPreview 
  href="https://example.com/article"
  title="Article Title from Metadata"
  description="Article description from meta tags"
  image="https://example.com/article/og-image.jpg"
>
  this article
</LinkWithPreview>
```

## What to Scrape

- **title**: `<title>` or `og:title`
- **description**: `<meta name="description">` or `og:description`
- **image**: `og:image` or first prominent image
- **siteName**: `og:site_name`
- **author**: Article author if available

## Implementation

Always use firecrawl-mcp to fetch metadata rather than manual entry to ensure accuracy and save time.
